def create_dataset(img_folder_abnormal, img_folder_normal):
    img_data_array=[]
    class_name=[]
    counter_1 = 0
    counter_2 = 0
   
    for file in os.listdir(img_folder_normal):
        image_path= os.path.join(img_folder_normal, file)
        image= cv2.imread( image_path, cv2.IMREAD_UNCHANGED)
        image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        image=cv2.resize(image, (IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH),interpolation = cv2.INTER_CUBIC)
        image=np.array(image)
        image = image.astype('uint8')
        #image /= 255 
        img_data_array.append(image)
        class_name.append(0)
        counter_1 += 1
    
    for file in os.listdir(img_folder_abnormal):
        image_path= os.path.join(img_folder_abnormal, file)
        image= cv2.imread(image_path, cv2.IMREAD_UNCHANGED)
        image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
        image=cv2.resize(image, (IMG_HEIGHT, IMG_WIDTH),interpolation = cv2.INTER_CUBIC)
        image=np.array(image)
        image = image.astype('uint8')
        #image /= 255 
        img_data_array.append(image)
        class_name.append(1)
        counter_2 += 1
        
    print("Se han almacenado {} imagenes con la etiqueta 0 -> (normal), del directorio: '{}'".
          format(counter_1, img_folder_normal))
    print("Se han almacenado {} imagenes con la etiqueta 1 -> (abnormal), del directorio: '{}'".
          format(counter_2, img_folder_abnormal))

    return np.array(img_data_array), np.array(class_name).reshape(len(class_name), 1)
        
        
def plot_prediction(n_epochs, mfit, cf_matrix, lab):
    N = n_epochs
    plt.style.use("ggplot")
    
    group_names = ['True '+lab[0],'False '+lab[1],'False '+lab[0],'True '+lab[1]]

    group_counts = ["{0:0.0f}".format(value) for value in
                    cf_matrix.flatten()]

    group_percentages = ["{0:.2%}".format(value) for value in
                         cf_matrix.flatten()/np.sum(cf_matrix)]

    labels = [f"{v1}\n{v2}\n{v3}" for v1, v2, v3 in
              zip(group_names,group_counts,group_percentages)]

    labels = np.asarray(labels).reshape(2,2)

    
    
    fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(8,18))
    fig.suptitle('Training Loss and Accuracy')
    
    ax1.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["accuracy"], label="train")
    ax1.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["val_accuracy"], label="val")
    ax1.set_title("Accuracy")
    ax1.set_xlabel("Epoch #")
    ax1.set_ylabel("Accuracy")
    ax1.legend(loc="lower right")
    
    ax2.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["loss"], label="train")
    ax2.plot(np.arange(0, N), mfit.history["val_loss"], label="val")
    ax2.set_title("Loss")
    ax2.set_xlabel("Epoch #")
    ax2.set_ylabel("Loss")
    ax2.legend(loc="upper right")
    
    ax3 = sns.heatmap(cf_matrix, annot=labels, fmt='', cmap='Blues')

    ax3.set_title('Confusion Matrix\n\n')
    ax3.set_xlabel('\nPredicted Values')
    ax3.set_ylabel('Actual Values ')

    ax3.xaxis.set_ticklabels(lab)
    ax3.yaxis.set_ticklabels(lab)
    
    plt.show()
    
def recall_m(y_true, y_pred):
    true_positives = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true * y_pred, 0, 1)))
    possible_positives = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true, 0, 1)))
    recall = true_positives / (possible_positives + K.epsilon())
    return recall

def precision_m(y_true, y_pred):
    true_positives = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_true * y_pred, 0, 1)))
    predicted_positives = K.sum(K.round(K.clip(y_pred, 0, 1)))
    precision = true_positives / (predicted_positives + K.epsilon())
    return precision

def f1_m(y_true, y_pred):
    precision = precision_m(y_true, y_pred)
    recall = recall_m(y_true, y_pred)
    return 2*((precision*recall)/(precision+recall+K.epsilon()))


lr_schedule = tf.keras.optimizers.schedules.ExponentialDecay(
    1e-4, decay_steps=430, decay_rate=0.95, staircase=True)

def unfreeze_model(model):
    for layer in model.layers:
        layer.trainable = True

    optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate=lr_schedule)#1e-4
    model.compile(
        optimizer=optimizer, loss="binary_crossentropy", metrics=["accuracy", f1_m,precision_m, recall_m]
    )

def plot_conf_matrix_binary(cf_matrix, lab):
    group_names = ['True '+lab[0],'False '+lab[1],'False '+lab[0],'True '+lab[1]]

    group_counts = ["{0:0.0f}".format(value) for value in
                    cf_matrix.flatten()]

    group_percentages = ["{0:.2%}".format(value) for value in
                         cf_matrix.flatten()/np.sum(cf_matrix)]

    labels = [f"{v1}\n{v2}\n{v3}" for v1, v2, v3 in
              zip(group_names,group_counts,group_percentages)]

    labels = np.asarray(labels).reshape(2,2)

    ax = sns.heatmap(cf_matrix, annot=labels, fmt='', cmap='Blues')

    ax.set_title('Confusion Matrix\n\n');
    ax.set_xlabel('\nPredicted Values')
    ax.set_ylabel('Actual Values ');

    ax.xaxis.set_ticklabels(lab)
    ax.yaxis.set_ticklabels(lab)
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

result_df = []
IMG_WIDTH=224
IMG_HEIGHT=224
dir_data = r"./data/"


for i in os.listdir(dir_data):
    print("--------------- STARTING ({}) TRAINING ---------------\n\n".format(i))
    train_dir_abnor = os.path.join(dir_data, i, "train/abnormal/")
    train_dir_nor = os.path.join(dir_data, i, "train/normal/")
    
    test_dir_abnor = os.path.join(dir_data, i, "test/abnormal/")
    test_dir_nor = os.path.join(dir_data, i, "test/normal/")
    
    valid_dir_abnor = os.path.join(dir_data, i, "valid/abnormal/")
    valid_dir_nor = os.path.join(dir_data, i, "valid/normal/")
    
    X_train, y_train = create_dataset(train_dir_abnor, train_dir_nor)
    X_test, y_test = create_dataset(test_dir_abnor, test_dir_nor)
    X_valid, y_valid = create_dataset(valid_dir_abnor, valid_dir_nor)
    
    saved_model_2 = load_model('best_model_2_b_2.h5')
    
    X_train, y_train = shuffle(X_train, y_train)
    X_test, y_test = shuffle(X_test, y_test)
    X_valid, y_valid = shuffle(X_valid, y_valid)
    
    train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
                            rotation_range=20,
                            zoom_range=0.15,
                            width_shift_range=0.2,
                            height_shift_range=0.2,
                            shear_range=0.15,
                            horizontal_flip=True,
                            fill_mode="nearest",
                            validation_split=0.2,
                            dtype = 'uint8')

    test_data_gen = ImageDataGenerator(dtype = 'uint8')
    


    unfreeze_model(saved_model_2)
    
    model_dir = r'./cv_models/'
    model_dir_ = os.path.join(model_dir, i, "best_model.h5")

    es = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', mode='min', verbose=1, patience=70)
    mc = ModelCheckpoint(model_dir_, monitor='val_accuracy', mode='max', verbose=1, save_best_only=True)

    hist = saved_model_2.fit(train_datagen.flow(X_train, y_train, batch_size=32),
                           epochs=200,
                           steps_per_epoch=X_train.shape[0]//32,
                           validation_steps=X_test.shape[0]//32,
                           validation_data=test_data_gen.flow(X_test, y_test),
                           verbose=2,
                           callbacks=[es, mc])

    saved_model_3 = load_model(model_dir_, custom_objects={"f1_m": f1_m, "recall_m": recall_m, "precision_m": precision_m })
    
    loss_train, accuracy_train, f1_score_train, precision_train, recall_train = saved_model_3.evaluate(X_train, y_train, verbose=0)
    loss_test, accuracy_test, f1_score_test, precision_test, recall_test = saved_model_3.evaluate(X_test, y_test, verbose=0)
    loss_valid, accuracy_valid, f1_score_valid, precision_valid, recall_valid = saved_model_3.evaluate(X_valid, y_valid, verbose=0)

    print('Train: %.3f, Test: %.3f, Valid: %3f' % (accuracy_train, accuracy_test, accuracy_valid))
    
    
    
    pred = saved_model_3.predict(X_valid)
    y_pred = ((pred > 0.5)+0).ravel()
    
    conf_mat = confusion_matrix(y_valid, y_pred, labels=[0,1])
    plot_prediction(len(hist.epoch), hist, conf_mat, ["normal", "abnormal"])
    
    matrix = classification_report(y_pred, y_valid)
    print('Classification report (test) : \n',matrix)
    
    print("\n\n--------------- ({}) TRAINING FINISHED ---------------\n\n".format(i))
    
    
    
    
    result_df.append([i, loss_test, accuracy_test, f1_score_test, precision_test, recall_test,
                      loss_valid, accuracy_valid, f1_score_valid, precision_valid, recall_valid])
